Value: A tetrahedron is a polyhedral shape defined by four triangular plane faces.
A cube is a polyhedral shape defined by six square plane faces.
An octahedron is a polyhedral shape defined by eight triangular plane faces.
An Icosahedron is a polyhedral shape defined by twenty triangular plane faces.
A dodecahedron is a polyhedral shape defined by with twelve pentagonal plane faces.
A cuboctahedron is a polyhedron with 8 triangular faces and 6 square faces.
A rhombicuboctahedron is a polyhedral shape defined by eighteen square faces and eight triangular faces, arranged symmetrically with twenty-four vertices.
A rhombic dodecahedron is a convex polyhedron with 12 congruent rhombic faces.
An anticuboctahedron is a polyhedral shape defined by 14 faces, comprising 8 triangles and 6 squares.
A trigonal bipyramid is a polyhedral shape defined by five triangular faces.
A triangular shape is a polygon defined by three edges and three vertices.
A trigonal prism is a polyhedral shape defined by two parallel triangular bases connected by three rectangular faces.
